he man, his unit, and the fight Alexander Jefferson fought so well.This revised edition covers the story of Jefferson’s continuing outreach and education work, as he brings the story of the Tuskegee Airmen to communities and schools across the country, and the presentation of the Congressional Gold Medal to the Airmen in 2007.Red Tail Captured, Red Tail Free is perhaps the only account of the African American experience in a German prison camp.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAfrican American fighter pilotsvBiography. 0aFighter pilotszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aPrisoners of warzGermanyvBiography. 0aPrisoners of warzUnited StatesvBiography. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945vPersonal narratives, American. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAerial operations, American. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xParticipation, African American. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xPrisoners and prisons, German. 4aAfrican American Studies. 4aRace & Ethnic Studies. 4aWorld War II. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh1 aCarlson, Lewis H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823274406?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823274406423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823274406/original  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK